Maiduguri – Governor Kashim Shettima of Borno State on Tuesday night announced the dissolution of the State Executive Council (SEC). The announcement was contained a letter issued by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Alhaji Usman Jidda Shuwa, and made available to newsmen on Wednesday. According to the press release, “The governor in accordance with the powers conferred on him by section 192 sub section 2 of the constitution of the Federal Republic of Nigeria as amended, has hereby dissolved the State Executive Council.” The SSG in the statement also directed that “all the commissioners are required by the law to handover the affairs of their ministries to their respective permanent secretaries on or before Friday, the 28th of September, 2018.” He conveyed the appreciation of the governor to the outgoing commissioners for their services and contributions to the developmental progress recorded by his administration. Shuwa further said that the governor wished all the former commissioners the best in their future endeavours. Meanwhile, five of the outgoing commissioners are aspiring for the governor’s office ahead of the 2019 election. , namely, Kaka Shehu Lawan of Justice; Adamu Lawan of Works and Transport, Mustapha Fannarambe of Religious Affairs and Professor Babagana Umara Zulum  of Reconstruction, Rehabilitation and Resettlement and Alh. Babagana Tigani Banki of Housing and Energy. Three are aspiring for the House of Representatives, namely, Dr. Haruna Mshela of Health, Dr. Zainab Gimba of Water Resources and Usman Zanna of Local Government and Emirate Affairs. The SSG further said a new State Executive Council would be constituted in due course. SHOCKING STORY!!! After 9 Years Of Suffering From Weak Erection & Premature Ejaculation, 43 Year Old Man Finally Discovers The Solution That Mysteriously Jerk His Dead Manhood Back To Life, Increased His "Rod" Size, And Now Last 32 Minutes In Bed. Click HERE! 